cell("markdown","### Chalkboard Defense\n1. Explain the time complexity of standard matrix multiplication for two $N \\times N$ matrices.\n2. Why is Numpy so much faster than our pure Python implementation?\n3. Explain how Exponentiation by Squaring works and prove its time complexity.\n\n<details><summary>💡 Sketch</summary>\n\n1. $O(N^3)$. There are $N^2$ elements to compute, and each requires a dot product of $N$ elements.\n2. Numpy uses highly optimized C/Fortran libraries (BLAS) that utilize CPU vector instructions (SIMD) and cache-friendly memory layouts.\n3. $A^k = (A^{k/2})^2$ if $k$ is even, or $A \\cdot (A^{(k-1)/2})^2$ if $k$ is odd. The number of multiplications halves at each step, taking $\\approx \\log_2(k)$ steps.\n</details>\n\n---\n📚 **Next:** Math 07 (Calculus — Differential Equations)")
